===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|remembren|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|remembrer||to remember|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{term|rememorari||to remember again|lang=la}}, from {{term|re-|lang=la}} + {{term|memor||mindful|lang=la}}, from Proto-Indo-European {{term/t|ine-pro|*mer-}}, {{term/t|ine-pro|*smer-||to think about, be mindful, remember}}. Cognate with {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|mimorian|lang=ang}}, {{term|mymerian||to remember, commemorate|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term/t|ang|māmorian||to deliberate, plan out, design}}. More at {{l|en|mammer}}.

{{rel-top|etymology note}}
The success of the [[Old French]] word was aided by its proximity in sound and meaning to an existing {{etyl|gem|en}} word: {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|mimorian|lang=ang}}, {{term|mymerian|lang=ang}} "to remember, commemorate" from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*mimrōną}}, {{term/t|gem-pro|*mīmrōną||to remember, be mindful}}, from the same {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} source, and is akin to {{etyl|frs|-}} ''[[mimerje|mīmerje]]'' "to ponder, reflect", {{etyl|gml|-}} ''[[mimeren|mīmeren, mīmern]]'' "to ponder, meditate", {{etyl|dum|-}} ''[[mimeren#Middle Dutch|mīmeren]]'' "to reflect, think to oneself" ({{etyl|nl|-}} ''[[mijmeren]]'' "to muse, reflect deeply"), [[Old English]] {{term|mimor||mindful|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|non|-}} ''[[Mímir]]'', ''[[Mim]]'', Norse god of Memory, [[Old English]] ''[[mamrian#Old English|māmrian]]'' "to think out, design". Related to {{l|en|mourn}}.

Displaced native {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|ȝemuneȝen||to remember|lang=enm|sc=Latinx}}, from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term/t|ang|ġemynegian||to remember, remind}}; {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term/t|enm|minnen||to remember, have in mind}}, from {{etyl|non|-}} {{term/t|non|minna||to remind}}; {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|munden|lang=enm}}, {{term|ȝemunden||to bear in mind, remember|lang=enm|sc=Latinx}}, from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term/t|ang|ġemynd||memory, remembrance}}; {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|ithenchen|lang=enm}}, {{term|ȝethenchen||to think on, remember|lang=enm|sc=Latinx}}, from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term/t|ang|ġeþencan}}; {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term/t|enm|manien||to remind, mention, remember}}, from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term/t|ang|manian||to admonish, remind, mention}}.
{{rel-bottom}}

